<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-25T05:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-25T05:35:00-05:00" n="491" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d491">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363/10–2544: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-25T14:00:00+03:25">October 25, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 3:33 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>781. Following is paraphrase of note I have received from Prime
                                Minister in reply to my note embodying substance of Department’s
                                622, October 16: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“I was exceedingly pleased to learn that the American
                                        Government has taken note of the fact that the Iranian
                                        Government’s decision to postpone the oil negotiations was
                                        done in good faith. I wish to express my Government’s
                                        appreciation. When the Iranian Government deems it advisable
                                        to reconsider the question of oil development the Embassy
                                        will be informed and it goes without saying that
                                        applications of American nationals will receive
                                        consideration.”</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>